---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Guest Preaching & Pulpit Fill | Scripture Alive"
  description="Be inspired by Jeremy's combination of dramatizing passages of Scriptures and preaching on them with practical and inspiring teaching."
  ogImage="https://cdn.sanity.io/images/vxczpihg/production/e43fbb6b224dc2ffef2c8abea65b96f1cea69bce-600x299.webp"
  jsonld={{
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebPage",
    "name": "Guest Preaching & Pulpit Fill",
    "url": "https://scripturealive.com/guestpreaching",
    "description": "Be inspired by Jeremy's combination of dramatizing passages of Scriptures and preaching on them with practical and inspiring teaching.",
    "about": {
      "@type": "Person",
      "name": "Jeremy Kluth",
      "jobTitle": "Speaker & Preacher",
      "worksFor": {
        "@type": "Organization",
        "name": "Scripture Alive",
        "url": "https://scripturealive.com"
      }
    }
  }}
>

  <!-- Hero / Intro Section -->
  <section class="py-12 px-4 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-accent font-display mb-4">
        Biblically-Rich Guest Speaking
      </h1>
      <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
        Powerful spoken messages for churches, chapels, camps, and podcasts —
        often paired with live Scripture performance and personal storytelling.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Elijah Section (image left, text right) -->
  <section class="py-8 px-4 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start">
        <div class="w-full md:w-5/12">
          <img
            src="https://scripturealive.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/5250fd1d140164a78500f1528b8bf5fb_1200_80.webp"
            alt="Elijah: God Provides in Tough Times"
            class="w-full object-cover"
            loading="eager"
            fetchpriority="high"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="w-full md:w-7/12">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800 font-serif mb-3">
            Elijah: God Provides in Tough Times
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Elijah's journey is filled with incredible stories of obedience, faith, and provision in the midst of a drought, a depression, and a departure as he is tested to trust in the word of the Lord. Any chapter from 1 Kings 17–2 Kings 2 can be chosen for a sermon, or all can be chosen for a retreat or camp week.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Daniel Section (text left, image right) -->
  <section class="py-8 px-4 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start">
        <div class="w-full md:w-7/12">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800 font-serif mb-3">
            Daniel: Being Godly in an Ungodly World
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            From a young teenager to an old man, Daniel sets us an example worthy to be emulated in his speech, in his conduct, in his love, in his faith, and in his purity, all while being forced to live in a culture of the ungodly. Any chapter from 1–6 can be chosen for a sermon, or all can be chosen for a retreat or camp week.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="w-full md:w-5/12">
          <img
            src="https://scripturealive.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/fc2616b23e584b651de5dff0be967042_1200_80.webp"
            alt="Daniel: Being Godly in an Ungodly World"
            class="w-full object-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Paul Section (image left, text right) -->
  <section class="py-8 px-4 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start">
        <div class="w-full md:w-5/12">
          <img
            src="https://scripturealive.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/ac2245f7ac879da4ce2650ce329ccd77_1200_80.webp"
            alt="Paul: Steadfastness & Stability in an Anxious World"
            class="w-full object-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="w-full md:w-7/12">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800 font-serif mb-3">
            Paul: Steadfastness &amp; Stability in an Anxious World
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            No matter the circumstance, whether it be imprisonment, being stoned, or being shipwrecked, Paul was a constant non-anxious presence wherever he went and a steadfast proclaimer of the Gospel to all he came in contact with, which gives us a blueprint for how we ought to act in our own world today. Chapters from Acts 9–28 can be chosen for a sermon, or the whole journey of Paul's life can be chosen for a retreat.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- John's Gospel Section (text left, image right) -->
  <section class="py-8 px-4 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start">
        <div class="w-full md:w-7/12">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800 font-serif mb-3">
            John's Gospel: That You May Believe
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            In this Gospel account, John recounts many of the miracles and teachings of Jesus in an effort to show His divinity that we may believe He truly is the Christ and that we might have life in His name. This is a five-part series that works well with retreats, but can also be modified as a sermon for a chapter or passage from John's Gospel.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="w-full md:w-5/12">
          <img
            src="https://scripturealive.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/St-John-Picture.jpg"
            alt="John's Gospel: That You May Believe"
            class="w-full object-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 1 Peter Section (image left, text right) -->
  <section class="py-8 px-4 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start">
        <div class="w-full md:w-5/12">
          <img
            src="https://scripturealive.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/St-Peter-Picture-V2.png"
            alt="1 Peter: Suffering for Christ"
            class="w-full object-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
        <div class="w-full md:w-7/12">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800 font-serif mb-3">
            1 Peter: Suffering for Christ
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Peter makes it clear that we should not be surprised at the fiery trial when it comes upon us to test us as though something strange was happening to us, but rather we are to rejoice insofar as we share Christ's sufferings. Christ set the standard for suffering well as a believer, so it's vital for us to learn how to suffer well as sojourners and exiles in this world. Can be any or all five chapters for a retreat or sermon.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Custom Programs/Sermons Section (text left, image right) -->
  <section class="py-8 px-4 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-6 items-start">
        <div class="w-full md:w-7/12">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-800 font-serif mb-3">
            Custom Programs/Sermons
          </h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            Doing a topical sermon series or an in-depth study of a narrative book like Genesis or Acts and want to stay on track? You can also request Jeremy to study and memorize a passage, chapter, or verses on a specific topic for his performance and preaching combination.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="w-full md:w-5/12">
          <img
            src="https://scripturealive.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/dbe310aea40d6e564f27cd08076e1234_1200_80.webp"
            alt="Custom Programs/Sermons"
            class="w-full object-cover"
            loading="lazy"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Invite Jeremy CTA -->
  <section class="py-10 px-4 bg-white">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto text-center">
      <a
        href="/contact"
        class="inline-block bg-accent text-white font-serif font-semibold px-8 py-3 rounded hover:bg-accent/85 transition-colors"
      >
        Invite Jeremy
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>